## Interpretation Pipeline

> **Implementation note.** The common-command path is fully **on-device and
> offline-capable**. The model is consulted only for ambiguous intent and is
> bounded by a hard timeout with local fallback — see `ARCHITECTURE.md` for the
> device/server boundary, which exists for privacy and reliability as much as
> for interpretation quality.

### Pipeline Stages

**Stage 0: Input Capture & Normalization**
- Accepts **typed text (primary)** or **voice (secondary, Web Speech API)**.
  Voice is never the only input path; a visible transcript and keyboard-
  accessible controls are always available. Empty input is handled explicitly.

**Stage 1: Local Deterministic Parser** — *on-device, primary*
- Normalizes the utterance and matches it against the supported command
  vocabulary with a confidence score. At minimum this path handles: dark mode
  on/off, text size up/down, contrast up/down, reduced motion on/off, simplify
  page, read aloud / stop, move content left/right, undo, reset — **with no
  network call.** The most common commands must work without the model.

**Stage 2: Model Fallback (Gemini Flash)** — *server-side, ambiguous intent only*
- Invoked only when local confidence is low. Receives **only** the user's
  command plus current settings — never page content, forms, passwords, or
  history. Returns **structured intent only**, never DOM/CSS/JS.

**Stage 3: Runtime Schema Validation (Zod)**
- Strict validation: reject unknown keys, enforce enum action types, bound all
  numerics, cap explanation length, reject impossible combinations, default
  missing values safely. Any non-conforming model output is rejected, not
  executed.

**Stage 4: Deterministic Action Engine**
- Maps the validated intent to **predefined, idempotent transforms.** Enabling
  dark mode twice produces no duplicate effect. No model-supplied selector, CSS,
  or code is ever executed.

**Stage 5: Reversibility & State Ledger**
- A single typed, serializable state object records every active adaptation and
  every injected node/style/overlay/observer. Undo is stack-based; **reset
  removes all extension-added classes, inline styles, overlays, reader
  containers, mutation observers, speech synthesis, highlighting, repositioning,
  and temporary wrappers**, restoring the original page completely.

**Stage 6: Explanation & Trace Generation**
- The explanation is generated **deterministically from the validated command**,
  not trusted from free-form model text: what you said → what was interpreted →
  what changed → why → local vs. model → confidence (when applicable) →
  processing time → what data left the device.

**Stage 7: Confidence Gate**
- No adaptation is applied on low-confidence intent; the app requests
  clarification instead. This is the plain-language equivalent of "I can't read
  that clearly" — the product declines rather than guesses.

