## Adaptation Library

### Flagship — Simplify This Page

The highest-value transform and the primary "wow." On requests such as "this
page is overwhelming" or "show me only what matters," the engine:
detects primary content via semantic HTML, ARIA roles, DOM structure, heading
hierarchy, and text/link-density heuristics; de-emphasizes navigation, ads,
sidebars, popups, cookie overlays, and decorative widgets; preserves important
interactive controls, useful images, and functional links; enlarges text,
increases spacing, and applies a readable width; and shows a visible explanation
of what changed — with one-click undo and full reset, **without permanently
modifying the page.** A robust fallback handles pages with no clear main content.

### Readability & Comfort

Text enlargement, line/paragraph/letter spacing, readable width, reading mode,
high contrast, dark/dim/warm modes, and reduced motion — each idempotent and
reversible, each applied as narrowly as practical to avoid breaking site layout.

### Focus, Structure & Repositioning

Focus highlighting, heading-hierarchy cleanup, and left/right content
repositioning ("move the important content to the right") that shifts the primary
reading column and practical controls while preserving keyboard navigation and
explaining what moved.

### Sensory & Output

**Read-aloud** (Web Speech API): read main content, pause/resume/stop, skip
section, read selection, and highlight the spoken section where practical —
skipping navigation clutter in simplified mode, with graceful fallback when
speech synthesis is unavailable. **Color Distinction Assistance:** increase
luminance contrast, add borders/patterns/labels to color-coded elements, and
reduce reliance on red-vs-green — applied conservatively, with **no claim of
clinical correction or vision restoration.**

