## Interface & Trust Surfaces

The popup / side panel is designed for a **non-technical user**, with large,
readable, keyboard-accessible controls and **plain language instead of technical
terminology** ("Larger text," "Less movement," "Simplify page," "Dim bright
colors," "Improve color distinction," "Move content right," "Read this page").

Suggested surfaces: voice/text command input with clear microphone and
listening/processing/error states; current active adaptations; quick actions;
Simplify Page; read-aloud controls; undo/reset; the **explanation trace panel**;
the **privacy panel**; the Assist / Simulation toggle; and an optional debug
metrics section. All text rendered into the UI is sanitized; no unsafe
`innerHTML`.

