## Reliability & Performance Engineering

### Reliability

Local command fallback; request timeout via `AbortController` (3–5 s) with
graceful failure; a **visible offline mode** and clear error states with no
infinite loading; idempotent commands; complete reset; undo history and state
restoration; protection against duplicate content-script injection; and handling
for dynamically rendered pages and single-page applications. When the model is
unavailable: *"AI interpretation is unavailable. Common accessibility commands
still work locally."*

### Performance

Local interpretation should feel near-instant and page transformations should
complete quickly. The engine avoids repeated full-page DOM scans, large mutation
loops, and unnecessary reflows; prefers targeted transforms over
whole-`body` filters; uses a **debounced, controlled `MutationObserver`** for
dynamic pages; and cleans up observers and injected elements on reset. A compact
debug panel exposes recent timings.

