## Technical Stack

> See `ARCHITECTURE.md` for full rationale.

| Component | Technology | Rationale |
|-----------|-----------|-----------|
| Extension Runtime | **Chrome Manifest V3, TypeScript** — content script + service worker + popup/side panel | Required target; minimum-permission model; shared TS types across UI, engine, and eval. |
| UI | **React** (reuse existing project UI), plain-language, keyboard-accessible controls | Non-technical usability; large readable controls; sanitized rendering. |
| Interpreter — primary | **Local deterministic parser (TS)** | Instant, offline, deterministic; covers the full common-command path with no network. |
| Interpreter — fallback | **Gemini Flash** via serverless API route, ambiguous intent only | Low-latency model; returns structured intent only; key stays server-side. |
| Validation | **Zod** (strict runtime schema) | Rejects unknown keys / unsafe or impossible model output before execution. |
| State & Persistence | Single typed state object → **`chrome.storage.local`**; in-memory undo stack; versioned | Serializable, restorable, idempotent; clean teardown on reset. |
| Action Engine | **Deterministic, reversible DOM/CSS transforms** (predefined only) | No model-authored code executes; every mutation is tracked and undoable. |
| Speech I/O | **Web Speech API** (TTS primary; STT secondary) | Browser-native, no server; graceful fallback when unsupported. |
| Server | **Next.js API route on Vercel** holding the model key | Validates + size-limits requests; returns validated intent; secret never client-side. |
| Evaluation | **Standalone Node/TS harness** + labeled JSON dataset | Reproducible, measured metrics; runs local-only when no key is present, labeling AI tests skipped. |

