## Market Positioning

AdaptAble positions itself as the **accessibility layer that adapts the web to
the person, in their own words** — filling the gap between browser settings that
demand technical vocabulary and overlay widgets that auto-inject and overclaim.
By meeting users in ordinary language, composing safe and reversible
adaptations, and explaining every change while keeping page content private, it
turns "I know this page is hard to use but I don't know how to fix it" into a
one-sentence request the browser can honor — and, unlike a compliance overlay,
it earns trust by being user-controlled, transparent, and honest about exactly
what it does and does not do.
